#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Interactive Claude session pre-cast as ds-designer.
# Run from its own iTerm pane. Talks to the other panes via designs/active/*.md.
set -euo pipefail
cd "$(dirname "$0")/.."
exec claude "You are playing the role of ds-designer for this session (interactive, not as a one-shot subagent).

FIRST: Read these three files in order, then summarize your role back to me in one sentence so I know you loaded:
1. .claude/agents/ds-designer.md
2. designs/context.md
3. (if it exists) designs/active/brief.md

After that, WAIT for my instructions before doing anything else. When I ask you to:
- 'write a brief' → produce/update designs/active/brief.md (create parent dirs if needed)
- 'critique' → read designs/active/implementation.md and designs/active/evaluation.md, then write designs/active/design-critique.md

Hard rule: do not edit anything under src/ or public/ — you are the designer, not the engineer.

Stay in this session. I may come back and iterate with you many times."
